algorithm: The new algorithm calculates the score for each bin as the product of the logarithm of the rest capacity of the bin, the square root of the item size plus the rest capacity of the bin, and the inverse of the rest capacity of the bin. The scores are then normalized to maintain self-consistency.
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    scores = np.log(bins) * np.sqrt(item + bins) * (1 / bins)
    scores /= np.sum(scores)
    return scores
